  "texts": [
    "We hope that our study adds an additional layer of caution when using LLMs for generating professional documents, and promotes the equitable and inclusive advancement of these intelligent systems.",
    "We use the default parameters of ChatGPT with OpenAI's chat completion API, which are \"GPT-3.5-Turbo\" with temperature, top_p, and n set to 1 and no stop token.",
    "For Alpaca, Vicuna, and Sta-bleLM, we configure the maximum number of new tokens to be 512, repetition penalty to be 1.5, temperature to be 0.1, top p to be 0.75, and number of beams to be 2.",
    "All configuration hyper-parameters are selected through parameter tuning experiments to ensure the best generation performance of each model.",
    "During reference letter generation, we observe that i) ChatGPT can always produce reasonable reference letters, and ii) other LLMs that we investigate sometimes fail to do so."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}